<subSubSection pageId="3" pageNumber="52" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="3.[151,1437,978,1365]" pageId="3" pageNumber="52">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,274,978,1004]" pageId="3" pageNumber="52">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
1) body orange, except the head, hind leg (proximal part of coxa orange), and posterior margins of tergites II–V and tergites VI+ black; 2) fore wing hyaline; 3) head, in dorsal view, with gena slightly convex behind eyes; 4) face smooth and without a carina; 5) occipital carina slightly upcurved and not reduced dorsally; 6) pronotum with the pocket-like structure not reduced longitudinally; 7) epicnemial carina vestigial ventrally; 8) sternite I with a low, rounded swelling posteriorly; 9) female with tarsal claw with square lobe, and with apex overtaking the lobe (tarsal claw single in males); 10) female with ovipositor sheath about 0.8 × as long as the hind tibia.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="3" pageNumber="52" type="distribution">
<paragraph blockId="3.[151,1437,978,1365]" box="[199,1241,1194,1221]" pageId="3" pageNumber="52">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,353,1194,1220]" pageId="3" pageNumber="52">Distribution.</emphasis>
<collectingCountry box="[359,431,1195,1221]" name="Brazil" pageId="3" pageNumber="52">Brazil</collectingCountry>
. This is the first record of the species and genus for 
<collectingCountry box="[1013,1124,1195,1221]" name="Argentina" pageId="3" pageNumber="52">Argentina</collectingCountry>
(
<figureCitation box="[1140,1228,1195,1221]" captionStart="FIGURE 7" captionStartId="9.[151,250,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox="[166,1420,181,1920]" captionTargetId="figure-16@9.[166,1421,181,1920]" captionTargetPageId="9" captionText="FIGURE 7. Geographical distribution of the Hymenoepimecis species. (A) H. atlantica sp. n.; (B) H. castilloi Pádua &amp; Sääksjärvi, 2020; (C) Hymenoepimecis japi Sobczak, Loffredo, Penteado-Dias &amp; Gonzaga, 2009; (D) H. ribeiroi Pádua &amp; Sobczak, 2015; (E) H. uberensis Pádua &amp; Onody, 2015; (F) H. veranii Loffredo &amp; Penteado-Dias, 2009." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6911289" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6911289/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="52">Fig. 7C</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="3.[151,1437,978,1365]" pageId="3" pageNumber="52">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,397,1230,1257]" pageId="3" pageNumber="52">Biological notes.</emphasis>
Parasitoid of the tetragnathid 
<taxonomicName authority="Mello-Leitao, 1943" authorityName="Mello-Leitao" authorityYear="1943" box="[755,1251,1231,1257]" class="Arachnida" family="Tetragnathidae" genus="Leucauge" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="3" pageNumber="52" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="roseosignata">
<emphasis box="[755,1019,1231,1256]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="52">Leucauge roseosignata</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Mello-Leitao, C. F." box="[1029,1251,1231,1257]" pageId="3" pageNumber="52" pagination="147 - 245" refId="ref4571" refString="Mello-Leitao, C. F. (1943) Catalogo das aranhas do Rio Grande do Sul. Arquivos do Museu Nacional do Rio de Janeiro, 37, 147 - 245." type="journal article" year="1943">Mello-Leitão, 1943</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Sobczak, J. F. &amp; Loffredo, A. P. S. &amp; Penteado-Dias, A. M. &amp; Gonzaga, M. O." pageId="3" pageNumber="52" pagination="2691 - 2699" refId="ref4994" refString="Sobczak, J. F., Loffredo, A. P. S., Penteado-Dias, A. M. &amp; Gonzaga, M. O. (2009) Two new species of Hymenoepimecis (Hymenoptera: Ichneumonidae: Pimplinae) with notes on their spider hosts and behaviour manipulation. Journal of Natural History, 43 (43 - 44), 2691 - 2699. https: // doi. org / 10.1080 / 00222930903244010" type="journal article" year="2009">
Sobczak 
<emphasis box="[1376,1429,1231,1257]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="52">et al</emphasis>
